Systematic development of four language skills (reading, writing, listening and speaking) in parallel with vocabulary and language teaching.Objectives/eesmärkid:  This course is for foreign students, who will start their studies in Estonian language and spend the first year learning only Estonian. The aim is to develop the level of Estonian language to the first  language proficiency level (0-> A2).Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student: - can manage in day-to-day communication situations that require direct and easy information exchange on familiar topics (eg information about yourself and the family, everyday activities, home, traffic, health, work); - knows the basic grammar of the Estonian language and uses it both in oral and in written expressions; - writes simple texts for an acquaintance or for an interesting topic; - describes experiences, events, desires and goals, and briefly / explains their views and plans.
